A police rescue dog, police officer and a family member of a missing person were attacked by a swarm of bees in Nongoma on the KwaZulu-Natal north coast at the weekend. The injured  dog, Dante, was airlifted to a veterinary hospital in Durban for emergency treatment. KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson Lt-Col Nqobile Gwala said a  report about a missing person was received at 9am on Saturday. “The dog and his handler proceeded to Nongoma area where a search was conducted. During the search, the member and his  dog and a family member were attacked by a swarm of bees. “The  dog was stung and  rushed to a veterinary hospital in Durban where he was treated and admitted.” Gwala said Dante had sustained critical injuries and seeking treatment from a vet who was available at the time was a matter of life and death. She said Dante, the police officer and family member were doing “fine”. TimesLIVE